        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer811179848" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18135619299125131314"> I&apos;m going to be bluntly honest. The prologue was really long and boring. So, I&apos;ve summed it up into 5 easy steps. <br/> 1. This good guy, got a sword from this bad guy.<br/> 2. He went crazy.<br/> 3. He killed a lot of people, including his wife.<br/> 4. Because he went crazy his son is deformed. So, he went back and killed the bad guy and busted up the sword into twelve pieces.<br/> 5. Collin and Glory are best friends and they got bored one day and decided to go play in the woods, even though the were told not to and</span>
  <span id="freeText18135619299125131314" style="display:none"> I'm going to be bluntly honest. The prologue was really long and boring. So, I've summed it up into 5 easy steps. <br /> 1. This good guy, got a sword from this bad guy.<br /> 2. He went crazy.<br /> 3. He killed a lot of people, including his wife.<br /> 4. Because he went crazy his son is deformed. So, he went back and killed the bad guy and busted up the sword into twelve pieces.<br /> 5. Collin and Glory are best friends and they got bored one day and decided to go play in the woods, even though the were told not to and the ran into a Donestre. It's a lion head on a man's body, like a Minotaur, but with a lion. Any ways, Collin fights the Done-thing and stabbed it in the eye. Then they went home with a broken knife and his daddy got really mad at him and won't let him back in, until he finds his dagger. So now he lives in the Glory's Pantry. The End. Of the prologue. Enjoy your story.</span>
