<div id="review_3846196305" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3846196305" />
    <a title="L" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/130509855-l"><img alt="L" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3846196305?book_show_action=true">Feb 18, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="L" class="user" itemprop="url" name="L" href="/user/show/130509855-l">L</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/130509855-l?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/130509855-l?shelf=ya">ya</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/130509855-l?shelf=retellings">retellings</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3846196305" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13730899113326039893">To all its readers, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/20423826.The_Subtle_Beauty' title='The Subtle Beauty by Ann Hunter' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Subtle Beauty</a> is obviously unrealistic. I was never swept into its story, captured by its characters, convinced in my heart that anything was happening.<br/><br/>Yet, somehow... I smile. The slight twists on Beauty and the Beast--in a land where no one is truly evil, regardless of the myths and backstories and plots we hear--culminate in a &apos;happily ever after&apos; hard to measure up to.</span>
  <span id="freeText13730899113326039893" style="display:none">To all its readers, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/20423826.The_Subtle_Beauty" title="The Subtle Beauty by Ann Hunter" rel="nofollow noopener">The Subtle Beauty</a> is obviously unrealistic. I was never swept into its story, captured by its characters, convinced in my heart that anything was happening.<br /><br />Yet, somehow... I smile. The slight twists on Beauty and the Beast--in a land where no one is truly evil, regardless of the myths and backstories and plots we hear--culminate in a 'happily ever after' hard to measure up to.</span>
